title: High Frequency Receiver (HFR) Field Waveform Samples in V/m (Selectable between the U, V and W Axes) - Craig Kletzing (University of Iowa)

info.x_cadence_note: Counts based on variable 'Epoch' in https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/sp_phys/data/rbsp/rbspb/l2/emfisis/hfr/waveform/2012/rbsp-b_hfr-waveform_emfisis-l2_20120901_v1.2.2.cdf. The most common cadence, 5999996781 [ns] = PT5.999997S, occurred for 30.7453% of the 99 timesteps.

parameters.name: HFRsamples_spec
parameters.description: V/m displayed as spectrogram of values vs time offsets. This variable is a 'virtual' variable that is computed using the function alternate_view (see https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/software/cdawlib/source/virtual_funcs.pro) on the with inputs of the variables ['HFRsamples']. Note that some COMPONENTS may not be available from the HAPI interface. They are accessible from the raw CDF files, however.

bins.name: timeOffsets_extended
bins.description: Time step, in ns, for each of the 32768 points referenced from the first point.

parameters.name: HBGain
parameters.description: Attenuator select indicator for U and V axis.  0-Off, 1-On.   Switches in a 19 dB attenuator.

parameters.name: HBSelect
parameters.description: ---> Axis channel indicator for the HFR.  0-U axis, 1-V axis, 2-W axis.

title: High Frequency Receiver (HFR) Field Waveform Samples in V/m (Selectable between the U, V and W Axes) - Craig Kletzing (University of Iowa)

parameters.name: HFRsamples_times
parameters.description: V/m displayed as very high resolution time-series. This variable is a 'virtual' variable that is computed using the function expand_wave_data (see https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/software/cdawlib/source/virtual_funcs.pro) on the with inputs of the variables ['HFRsamples', 'Epoch', 'timeOffsets']. Note that some COMPONENTS may not be available from the HAPI interface. They are accessible from the raw CDF files, however.
